      "It is tempting to file reading under one subject — the English lesson, the reading corner, the literacy hour — and treat the rest of the school day as something else. But a moment's thought dissolves the division. A child reads a science experiment, a history source, a word problem in maths, an instruction in art. Reading is not one subject among many; it is the medium through which nearly every other subject is learned. Treating literacy as everyone's responsibility, in every lesson, transforms both reading and learning.",
